	The Production Reliability Problem
	
	RUNNING vs Actually Working
	
	The Problem:
	
	A container can be "running" but the application inside is broken
	
	Database is up but, not accepting connections
	Wb server running but returning 500 errors
	Application deadlocked or infinite loop
	
	Container status shows "Up" but user can't access the service!
	
	What we need 
	
	1. Healthchecks - Verify the application is actually working
	2. Restart Policies - Automatically recover from failures

Without these : Manual intervention required for every failure

Docker Restart Policies

Four restart policies:

no(default) : Never restart automatically :- docker run --restart=no nginx

On-failure : Restart only if container exits with error (non-zero exit code) :- docker run --restart=on-failure nginx 

always: Always restart, even if stopped manually (restart on daemon startup) :- docker run --restart=always nginx

unless-stopped : Always restart, unless explicitly stopped by user :- docker run --restart=unless-stopped nginx

Docker Healthchecks - Monitoring Application Health

What is a healthcheck ?

	• A command Docker runs periodically to check if the container is health 

	• Returns exit code 0 = 0 healthy, non-zero = unhealthy

	• Can trigger restarts or alerts

What this means:

	• Check every 30 second

	• Timeout after 3 seconds

	• Fail after 3 consecutive failures

	• Command: curl the app, exit 1 if it fails


In Dockerfile:

HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=3s --retires=3s CMD curl -f http://localhost/  || exit 1





